</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">CorVision</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><script>function mfTempOpenSection(id){var block=document.getElementById("mf-section-"+id);block.className+=" open-block";block.previousSibling.className+=" open-block";}</script><table class="infobox vevent" style="width:22em">
<caption class="summary">CorVision</caption>
<tr>
<th scope="row"><a href="/wiki/Software_developer" title="Software developer">Developer</a></th>
<td class="organiser">Cortex</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">First&#160;appeared</th>
<td>1986<span style="display:none">&#160;(<span class="bday dtstart published updated">1986</span>)</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background-color: #eee;">Influenced by</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/Inform" title="Inform">Inform</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>CorVision</b> is a fourth generation <a href="/wiki/Computer_programming" title="Computer programming">programming</a> tool (<a href="/wiki/4GL" class="mw-redirect" title="4GL">4GL</a>) currently owned by <a href="/wiki/Attunity" title="Attunity">Attunity, Inc.</a> CorVision was developed by Cortex Corporation for the <a href="/wiki/OpenVMS" title="OpenVMS">VAX/VMS</a> <a href="/wiki/ISAM" title="ISAM">ISAM</a> environment. Although Cortex <a href="/wiki/Software_release_life_cycle#Beta" title="Software release life cycle">beta tested</a> CorVision-10 which was generated for PCs but CorVision itself stayed anchored on VMS. CorVision-10 proved more difficult than hoped, and was never released.</p>
<p></p>
